This paper deals with communication over multiple access channels with adversarial users, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several sub-fields in computer science. The most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory), as the paper focuses on capacity regions and coding schemes for reliable communication in the presence of an adversary. The paper also deals with security and authentication, which suggests categories such as cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper's use of randomized and deterministic codes suggests categories such as cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
